2024
02:36:59,420 --> 02:37:01,410
'Get back, you fools!

2025
02:37:01,410 --> 02:37:07,780
Can't you see she's trying to save herself
by lies?' he thundered.

2026
02:37:07,780 --> 02:37:14,620
'How can she give information about me when
she knows nothing?

2027
02:37:14,620 --> 02:37:18,021
She's never walked the 11 miles to Launceston.

2028
02:37:18,021 --> 02:37:21,561
Look at her feet.

2029
02:37:21,561 --> 02:37:27,870
She's been with a man somewhere down the road,
and he sent her back on wheels.

2030
02:37:27,870 --> 02:37:30,271
Get up!'

2031
02:37:30,271 --> 02:37:32,990
He pulled her to her feet.

2032
02:37:32,990 --> 02:37:38,050
Then he pointed to the sky, where the low
clouds were blown by the wind and a single

2033
02:37:38,050 --> 02:37:39,320
star shone.

2034
02:37:39,320 --> 02:37:41,061
'Look there!

2035
02:37:41,061 --> 02:37:45,080
There's a break in the sky, and the wind's
going east.

2036
02:37:45,080 --> 02:37:52,090
There'll be more wind still, and a wild grey
morning on the coast in six hours' time.

2037
02:37:52,090 --> 02:37:55,301
We'll waste no more time here.

2038
02:37:55,301 --> 02:38:02,670
Come on, you lazy devils, don't you want to
