2079
02:41:03,311 --> 02:41:06,640
could see only for a few yards.

2080
02:41:06,640 --> 02:41:11,000
She tried the handle of the carriage door,
but it was locked.

2081
02:41:11,000 --> 02:41:13,880
Then she listened.

2082
02:41:13,880 --> 02:41:17,950
Carried up towards her on the wind came the
sound of the sea.

2083
02:41:17,950 --> 02:41:21,440
The valley clearly led down to the shore.

2084
02:41:21,440 --> 02:41:24,000
Mary trembled.

2085
02:41:24,000 --> 02:41:31,261
Somewhere in the darkness below, her uncle
and his companions were waiting for the tide.

2086
02:41:31,261 --> 02:41:34,170
Mary considered the size of the window.

2087
02:41:34,170 --> 02:41:40,360
The door was locked, she knew, but she might
force her body through the narrow window frame.

2088
02:41:40,360 --> 02:41:46,280
She struggled and pushed, and then finally
she lost her balance and fell to the ground

2089
02:41:46,280 --> 02:41:47,280
below.

2090
02:41:47,280 --> 02:41:53,251
The drop was nothing, but the fall shook her
and she felt blood run down her side where

2091
02:41:53,251 --> 02:41:56,120
the window had caught her.

2092
02:41:56,120 --> 02:42:00,890
She gave herself a moment to rest, and then
she dragged herself to her feet and began

2093
02:42:00,890 --> 02:42:06,550
to move uncertainly along the track, in the
dark shelter of the bank.

2094
02:42:06,550 --> 02:42:11,021
She had not yet formed a plan, but, with her
back turned away from the sea, she would be

2095
02:42:11,021 --> 02:42:14,230
putting distance between herself and the men.

2096
02:42:14,230 --> 02:42:19,801
This track, leading upwards and to the left,
would take her to the high ground above the

2097
02:42:19,801 --> 02:42:21,760
beach.

2098
02:42:21,760 --> 02:42:27,530
She felt her way along the path, sometimes
almost falling on loose stones, her hair blowing

2099
02:42:27,530 --> 02:42:28,640
into her eyes.

2100
02:42:28,640 --> 02:42:34,860
Turning a sharp corner, she put up her hands
to push back the loose curls from her eyes,

2101
02:42:34,860 --> 02:42:40,670
and because of this, she did not see a man
kneeling against the bank with his back towards

2102
02:42:40,670 --> 02:42:44,680
her, his eyes watching the track ahead.

2103
02:42:44,680 --> 02:42:50,010
She came against him, knocking the breath
from his body, and he, taken by surprise,

2104
02:42:50,010 --> 02:42:53,490
fell with her, crying out in fear and anger.

2105
02:42:53,490 --> 02:43:01,050
They fought on the ground, her hands tearing
at his face, but he was too strong for her.

2106
02:43:01,050 --> 02:43:08,920
He leant on her, breathing heavily, and then
he looked closely at her, showing broken yellow

2107
02:43:08,920 --> 02:43:09,920
teeth.

2108
02:43:09,920 --> 02:43:12,510
It was Harry the pedlar.

2109
02:43:12,510 --> 02:43:18,051
He expected her to cry or struggle but when
she did neither, he moved his weight on to

2110
02:43:18,051 --> 02:43:22,370
his arm and smiled at her in an ugly way.

2111
02:43:22,370 --> 02:43:25,830
'Didn't expect to see me, did you?

2112
02:43:25,830 --> 02:43:30,240
Thought I was down on the shore with the landlord
and the rest!

2113
02:43:30,240 --> 02:43:36,080
But now you re here, I'll make you very welcome.'

2114
02:43:36,080 --> 02:43:38,670
He was smiling still.

2115
02:43:38,670 --> 02:43:44,170
She moved quickly, striking out at him, and
hit him hard on the chin.

2116
02:43:44,170 --> 02:43:50,260
In a second, she had struggled from under
him and pulled herself to her feet.

2117
02:43:50,260 --> 02:43:55,670
She searched for a stone to throw at him,
but finding nothing but loose earth and sand,

2118
02:43:55,670 --> 02:44:01,040
she scattered this in his face and eyes, so
that he was blinded for a moment.

2119
02:44:01,040 --> 02:44:07,250
Then she turned again, and began to run like
a hunted thing up the twisting track, her

2120
02:44:07,250 --> 02:44:13,010
mouth open, her hands outstretched, falling
over the stones in the path, all sense of

2121
02:44:13,010 --> 02:44:17,510
direction gone, her one idea to escape from
Harry the pedlar.

2122
02:44:17,510 --> 02:44:24,420
A wall of mist closed in on her, blocking
out the distant line of bushes at which she,

2123
02:44:24,420 --> 02:44:30,230
had been aiming, and she stopped immediately,
