2131
02:45:03,510 --> 02:45:09,290
The breaking waves, though she could not see
them, were somewhere out in the darkness,

2132
02:45:09,290 --> 02:45:14,540
and to her surprise it seemed that they were
on a level with her, not beneath her.

2133
02:45:14,540 --> 02:45:21,340
This meant that the track must have been only
a few yards from the sea itself.

2134
02:45:21,340 --> 02:45:25,180
The high banks had cut off the sound of the
waves.

2135
02:45:25,180 --> 02:45:31,010
Just as she decided this, there was a break
in the mist ahead of her.

2136
02:45:31,010 --> 02:45:39,660
Directly in front of her were the high waves
breaking on the shore.

2137
02:45:39,660 --> 02:45:45,050
After a time, when her eyes had become used
to the shadows, she saw, grouped against a

2138
02:45:45,050 --> 02:45:52,780
large rock on the beach, a small number of
men, silently looking ahead into the darkness.

2139
02:45:52,780 --> 02:45:56,851
Their stillness made them more threatening.

2140
02:45:56,851 --> 02:45:57,851
She waited.

2141
02:45:57,851 --> 02:46:00,771
They did not move.

2142
02:46:00,771 --> 02:46:06,940
The mist began to lift very slowly, showing
the shape of the coastline.

2143
02:46:06,940 --> 02:46:12,810
To the right, in the distance, where the highest
part of the rocks sloped to the sea, Mary

2144
02:46:12,810 --> 02:46:14,950
could just see a light.

2145
02:46:14,950 --> 02:46:17,820
At first, she thought it was a star.

2146
02:46:17,820 --> 02:46:23,240
But then she realized with a shock that it
was a false light placed there by her uncle

2147
02:46:23,240 --> 02:46:24,420
and his companions.

2148
02:46:24,420 --> 02:46:30,830
They waited, all of them, standing on the
stones with the waves breaking beyond their

2149
02:46:30,830 --> 02:46:32,420
feet.

2150
02:46:32,420 --> 02:46:34,480
Mary watched with them.

2151
02:46:34,480 --> 02:46:38,960
Then out of the cloud and darkness came another
